==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Musette
<hw>Mu*sette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., dim. of OF.
<ets>muse</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small bagpipe formerly in
use, having a soft and sweet tone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An air adapted to this instrument; also, a kind of
rustic dance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Museum</ent>⟦br⟧
